# Moonlanding Platform - Production Reference

## Executive Summary

**Moonlanding** is an ultra-minimal unified platform for engagement management, document review, and collaboration. Built with zero-build architecture (tsx runtime), SQLite, and Lucia authentication.

**Status:** Production Ready  
**Architecture:** Zero-build, no vendor lock-in  
**Deployment:** Single Node.js server  

---

## Implemented Features (15 Complete)

1. Core Platform Runtime
2. Entity Management
3. Review and Engagement System
4. PDF Management
5. Collaboration Features
6. Email and Notifications
7. User Interface (66 components)
8. Data Import and Export
9. Configuration System
10. Google Integration
11. Role-Based Access Control
12. Chat System
13. PDF Annotations
14. Audit Trail and Action Logging
15. RFI System

**STATUS: All features fully implemented and production-ready. No pending work items remain.**

---

## Architecture & Technical Stack

| Component | Technology | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Runtime | tsx | Zero-build, runtime transpilation |
| Database | SQLite | better-sqlite3, local persistence |
| Authentication | Lucia + Arctic | OAuth integration |
| HTTP Server | Node.js custom | No framework bloat |
| Module Reloading | Custom cache invalidation | Hot reloading support |
| UI Components | RippleUI (40KB) | 66 total components |
| PDF Handling | Puppeteer | Rendering and annotations |
| Email | Nodemailer | SMTP-based transactional |
| Google Services | googleapis | Service account auth |
| Access Control | 5-role RBAC | 102+ granular permissions |

